  "time_ut": 1658134752,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dc0 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0d9a\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The responsibilities of the new president are explained",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Karu Jayasuriya, Chairman of the National Movement for a Fair Society, states that the first responsibility of the new president and the government should be to provide solutions to the crisis facing the country with a common consensus.",
        "Mr. Jayasuriya also stated in an announcement that the responsibility of drafting a new constitution that will lead to the development of the country in place of the existing constitution, which fully protects the democratic principles and safeguards the rights of the people, will be an important responsibility assigned to the new universal government.",
        "\"As a country, we have reached a critical point in order to choose a new leadership for our motherland. We consider it as an extremely responsible and responsible task and the main principle to be followed is that it should be done in accordance with the existing constitution.",
        "Today, that responsibility has been assigned to the Parliament of our country. Accordingly, as public representatives of this country, we expect that every member of parliament will fulfill their responsibility intelligently according to their conscience for the future well-being of the country. We also believe that there will be a consensus approach to provide a solution to the critical crisis that this country is facing today."
      ],
